1. docker build -t myapp:v1 . — build an image from a Dockerfile.

2. docker tag myapp:v1 myapp:latest — create an additional tag.

3. docker volume create mydata — create a persistent volume.

4. docker run -v mydata:/data myapp:latest — mount a volume into a container.

5. docker compose up -d — start all services defined in a docker-compose.yml file.

6. docker compose ps — view the status of the services.

7. docker compose down — stop and remove the stack.
